    "167": {
      "play": "Now will I stir this gamester. I hope I shall see an",
      "notes": [
        "Gamester] STEEVENS: In the present instance and in some others, this does not mean a man viciously addicted to games of chance, but a frolicsome person. [The meaning is probably more specific here, and Caldecott is nearer right in defining it as ‘disposed to try his fortune at this game.’ In the story of Faustina the Empresse in Painter’s Palace of Pleasure, gladiators are said to be ‘a certaine sort of gamsters in Rome, which we terme to bee maisters of defence,’ ii, p. 104, ed. Haslewood.—ED.]"
      ]
