      "notes": []
    },
    "51": {
      "play": "when Fortune makes Nature’s natural the",
      "notes": []
    },
    "52": {
      "play": "cutter-off of Nature’s wit.",
      "notes": []
    },
    "53": {
      "play": "CELIA: Peradventure this is not Fortune’s work neither,",
      "notes": []
    },
    "54": {
      "play": "but Nature’s, who perceiveth our natural wits too",
      "notes": [
        "reason of] That is, talk, discuss concerning. For the use of 'of,' as equivalent to about, concerning, see also V, iv, 59; or Mer. of Ven. I, iii, 54: 'I am debating of my present store,' or Abbott, § 174. See also Mer. of Ven. II, viii, 30: 'I reason'd with a Frenchman yesterday,' that is, talked."
      ]
    },
    "55": {
      "play": "dull to reason of such goddesses, and hath sent",
      "notes": []
