    "117": {
      "play": "LE BEAU: There comes an old man and his three sons—",
      "notes": [
        "There comes] ABBOTT, § 335: When the subject is as yet future, and, as it were, unsettled, the third person singular might be regarded as the normal inflection. Such passages are very common, particularly in the case of ‘There is.’ See Oth. I, i, 188: ‘Is there not charms.’ See also V, ii, 76 of the present play."
      ]
    },
    "118": {
      "play": "CELIA: I could match this beginning with an old tale.",
      "notes": []
    },
