    "124": {
      "play": "the Duke’s wrestler, which Charles in a moment",
      "notes": [
        "which Charles] ABBOTT, § 269: Which being an adjective frequently accompanies the repeated antecedent, where definiteness is desired or where care must be taken to select the right antecedent. This repetition is, perhaps, more common with the definite ‘the which.’ See post II, i, 36; II, vii, 125."
      ]
