    "208": {
      "play": "ORLANDO: You mean to mock me after, you should not",
      "notes": [
        "You meane] THEOBALD (Lit. Illust. ii, 329): Should not this be ‘An’ you mean,’ &c.? MASON (p. 82): I believe we should read, ‘If you mean;’ &c. CAMBRIDGE EDITORS (to whom Theobald’s conj. had occurred independently) remark (Note v): And for ‘an’ is a more probable reading than if, as it may have been omitted by the printer, who mistook it for part of the stage direction—‘Orl. and’ for ‘Orland.’"
