    "60": {
      "play": "Not to seem senseless of the bob. If not,",
      "notes": [
        "bob] DYCE: A taunt, a scoff. ‘A bob, sanna,’ Coles’s Lat. and Eng. Dict. WRIGHT: Cotgrave: ‘Taloche: A bob, or a rap ouer the fingers ends closed together.’",
        "If not] JOHNSON: Unless men have the prudence not to appear touched with the sarcasms of a jester, they subject themselves to his power; and the wise man will have his folly ‘anatomised,’ that is, dissected and laid open, by the ‘squandering glances’ or random shots of a fool.",
        "If not] JOHNSON: Unless men have the prudence not to appear touched with the sarcasms of a jester, they subject themselves to his power; and the wise man will have his folly ‘anatomised,’ that is, dissected and laid open, by the ‘squandering glances’ or random shots of a fool."
      ]
    },
