    "85": {
      "play": "That says his bravery is not on my cost,",
      "notes": []
    },
    "86": {
      "play": "Thinking that I mean him, but therein suits",
      "notes": [
        "Walker (Vers. 116) among instances of the shifting accent of wherein, whereof, &c. cites this line, but reads ‘Thus then’ for ‘There then.’ Dyce (ed. iii) says Lettsom conjectures ‘Where [sic Malone—ED.] then? how then? what then? let’s see wherein.’ [The line is inflexibly, and I believe intentionally, trochaic.—ED.]"
      ]
