    "87": {
      "play": "His folly to the mettle of my speech?",
      "notes": []
    },
    "88": {
      "play": "There then. How then, what then? Let me see",
      "notes": []
    },
    "89": {
      "play": "wherein",
      "notes": []
    },
    "90": {
      "play": "My tongue hath wronged him. If it do him right,",
      "notes": []
    },
    "91": {
      "play": "Then he hath wronged himself. If he be free,",
      "notes": [
        "free] DYCE: Free from vicious taint, guiltless. As in ‘Make mad the guilty and appal the free.’—Ham. II, ii, 590."
      ]
