    "201": {
      "play": "ROSALIND: Nay, I prithee now, with most petitionary",
      "notes": [
        "encounter] Grey (i, 181): A plain allusion to the following incident mentioned by Pliny, Hist. Nat. ii, 83 [or as it stands in Holland’s translation, cited by Tollet, but no credit given to Grey]: ‘There hapned once . . . . a great strange wonder of the earth; for two hils encountered together, charging, as it were, and with violence assaulting one another, yea, and retrying againe with a most mighty noise.’ Wright: There is of course no necessity for supposing that Shakespeare had such a passage in his mind."
