    "217": {
      "play": "ROSALIND: Is he of God’s making? What manner of",
      "notes": [
        "Gods making] WRIGHT: Or his tailor’s? Compare Lear, II, ii, 59: ‘nature disclaims in thee: a tailor made thee.’ Stephens in his Essays and Characters (2d ed. 1615) has one ‘My Mistresse,’ of whom he says: ‘Her body is (I presume) of God’s making & yet I cannot tell, for many parts thereof she made her selfe’ (p. 391). [Compare too what Viola answers (Twelfth N. I, v, 254) when Olivia unveils her face and asks, ‘is’t not well done?’ ‘Excellently done,’ replies Viola, ‘if God did all.’—ED.]"
      ]
    },
