    "244": {
      "play": "CELIA: It is as easy to count atomies as to resolve the",
      "notes": [
        "Atomies] MALONE: ‘An atomie,’ says Bullokar, in his Expositor, 1616, ‘is a mote flying in the sunne. Any thing so small that it cannot be made lesse.’ [Probably this was pronounced atomeis. In Sylvester’s Du Bartas, Bethuliæ Rescue, 1632, lib. vi, 346: ‘Alas! I erre: for all in Atomies Weret hou divided, all would not suffice.’ Again, Ibid., Battail of Yury, 421: ‘Our State (yerst honour’d where the Sun doth rise) Would fly in sparks or die in atomies.’ Also in R. L.’s Diella, Sonn. xxx., quoted by Caldecott (not, however, in reference to the pronunciation of atomie), we read: ‘Hee that can count the candles of the skie Or number nomberlesse small atomie.’—ED.]"
      ]
