    "263": {
      "play": "CELIA: You bring me out.",
      "notes": [
        "I would] See Abbott, § 329, for other examples of ‘would’ used for will, wish, require.",
        "bring me out] Almost a repetition of what she had just said; which explains itself. WRIGHT cites: Lowe's Lab. L. V. ii, 171: 'They do not mark me, and that brings me out.' If the reference in the present instance be not exclusively to music, our modern idiom has merely substituted put for 'bring.'—ED."
      ]
