    "391": {
      "play": "have not; a blue eye and sunken, which you have",
      "notes": [
        "blew eie] STEEVENS: That is, blueness about the eyes. WHITE: That is, hollow-eyed. ‘Blue eyes’ were called grey in Shakespeare’s time. See ‘blue-eyed hag,’ Temp. I, ii, 270."
