    "394": {
      "play": "you for that, for simply your having in beard is a",
      "notes": [
        "hauing] STEEVENS: ‘Having’ is possession, estate. So in Merry Wives, III, ii, 73: ‘The gentleman is of no having.’ [For nine or ten other examples see Schmidt.]"
      ]
