    "28": {
      "play": "AUDREY: Would you not have me honest?",
      "notes": []
    },
    "29": {
      "play": "TOUCHSTONE: No, truly, unless thou wert hard-favored;",
      "notes": [
        "hard fauour’d] COWDEN-CLARKE: These words show that Audrey was not uncomely; although she in her modesty, and Touchstone in his pleasantry, choose to make her out to be plain. It is evident that the court-jester had the wit to perceive something genuinely and intrinsically attractive about the girl, beneath her simple looks and manner. Besides, she was an oddity, and that had charms for him. Moreover, she evidently idolises him; which rivets him to her."
      ]
    },
    "30": {
