        "defence] STEEVENS: ‘Defence,’ as here opposed to ‘no skill,’ signifies the art of fencing. Thus, ‘and gave you such a masterly report, for arts and exercise in your defence.’—Ham. IV, vii, 98. CALDECOTT: Any means of defence is better than a lack of science; in proportion as something is to nothing. [Steevens’s is the better interpretation, I think.—ED.]"
      ]
