        "pageant] WHITER (p. 56): The ‘pageant’ of love seems to have been impressed on the mind of our poet. So in Mid. N. D. III, ii, 112, Puck speaks of ‘the youth, mistook by me, Pleading for a lover’s fee. Shall we their fond pageant see?’"
