      "notes": [
        "sauce] ROLFE: Cf. our vulgarism of 'sassing' a person. From meaning to give zest or piquancy to language, the word came to be used ironically in the sense of making it hot and sharp; or, in other words, from meaning to spice, it came to mean to pepper."
