    "40": {
      "play": "Look you lisp and wear strange suits, disable all",
      "notes": [
        "lispe] See Mercutio's invective against Tybalt.—Rom. & Jul. II, iv, 26, Wright: See Overbury's Characters (Works, p. 58, ed. Fairholt), where 'An Affectate Traveller' is described: 'He censures all things by countenances, and shrugs, and speakes his owne language with shame and lisping.' [Sig. F, ed. 1627. Over-"
      ]
