    "200": {
      "play": "tongue of yours won me. ’Tis but one cast away, and",
      "notes": [
        "come death] It is not impossible that there is here just an allusion to that popular song of Anne Bullen’s: ‘Death, rock me asleep. Bring me to quiet rest,’ &c. It sounds to me like some quotation or allusion, whose popularity excuses, or at least lightens, the charming exaggeration.—Ed."
