      ]
    },
    "70": {
      "play": "copulatives, to swear and to forswear, according as",
      "notes": [
        "copulatives] WRIGHT: Who desire to be joined in marriage. For the force of the termination -ive in Shakespeare see III, ii, 11."
      ]
    },
    "71": {
      "play": "marriage binds and blood breaks. A poor virgin, sir,",
      "notes": []
    },
    "72": {
      "play": "an ill-favored thing, sir, but mine own. A poor",
      "notes": []
    },
    "73": {
      "play": "humor of mine, sir, to take that that no man else",
      "notes": []
    },
    "74": {
      "play": "will. Rich honesty dwells like a miser, sir, in a poor",
      "notes": [
        "honestie] Again used as Celia and Audrey have used it before."
      ]
