      "notes": [
        "all . . . restored] WRIGHT: This may be grammatically explained either by regarding it as a continuation of the sentence in line 165, ‘was converted,’ the intervening line being parenthetical; or by supposing an ellipsis of were, ‘all their lands were restored’; or, which seems best, as an independent participial clause, ‘all their lands being restored.’"
      ]
