        "Sir] Capell: To the duke; putting himself, without ceremony, between him and de Boys, and then addressing the latter: and the subject of this address is the most admirable expedient for Jaques to make his exit in character that ever human wit could have hit upon; nor can the drama afford an example in which Horace’s servetur ad immut has been better observ’d than in this instance."
