        "bush] STEEVENS: It appears formerly to have been the custom to hang a tuft of ivy at the door of a vintner. I suppose ivy was chosen rather than any other plant, as it has relation to Bacchus. So in Gascoigne’s Glass of Government, 1575:"
      ]
